snippet.textDisplay: Dont get me wrong, I LOVE Samsung devices, and how they've come a long way with new technology yearly, but this idea of "folding" devices needs to end. A flexible OLED display is great, but not if it needs protection layers and breaks very easily. There is no reason a device should cost $1000 or more and break so quick. In fact there is no reason a device should be so fragile that it really cant be used daily - when its a device that WILL be used daily. Moto, Samsung, Huawei, etc - Stop releasing folding devices until either OLED panels can't be damaged on their own so easily or until actual plastics and glasses can finally bend logically without cracking, breaking, denting, scratching. Id rather wait another 2, 3 or 4 years until the tech is perfected than to have a device that breaks within days. The "one time" replacement cost of something so fragile really shouldn't be a "one time" replacement either. If a company knows it will break, they have a duty to replace it as many times as it takes.
snippet.textOriginal: Dont get me wrong, I LOVE Samsung devices, and how they've come a long way with new technology yearly, but this idea of "folding" devices needs to end. A flexible OLED display is great, but not if it needs protection layers and breaks very easily. There is no reason a device should cost $1000 or more and break so quick. In fact there is no reason a device should be so fragile that it really cant be used daily - when its a device that WILL be used daily. Moto, Samsung, Huawei, etc - Stop releasing folding devices until either OLED panels can't be damaged on their own so easily or until actual plastics and glasses can finally bend logically without cracking, breaking, denting, scratching. Id rather wait another 2, 3 or 4 years until the tech is perfected than to have a device that breaks within days. The "one time" replacement cost of something so fragile really shouldn't be a "one time" replacement either. If a company knows it will break, they have a duty to replace it as many times as it takes.
